{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778184266,"nonce":"lL7IFMPDjwj+rW1Udx+ELhpYvrc=","title":"Replace feedbax_rnn_controller with feedbax_graph_controller (post-eager-graph API); audit recent code for old-API assumptions","message":"Background: feedbax's eager-graph cutover (commit `1e5d8ec` on develop, Jan 2026) replaced the old staged-model + Iterator architecture with a unified `Graph` where cycles are auto-detected and `_call_with_iteration` runs `lax.scan` internally. Sensory feedback wiring lives inside the graph as explicit `Wire` objects, not in an external Iterator. Per-step evaluation is available via `Graph._call_single_step(inputs, state, key=key)`.\n\nThe induced-gain analyser (`74bfd86`, merged in `aa60d3f`) shipped a `feedbax_rnn_controller(step_fn, h0)` adapter that assumes the caller hand-extracts a pure step closure — this was implicitly modelled on the *old* staged API. With the new graph API, this is unnecessary.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Replace `feedbax_rnn_controller(step_fn, h0)` adapter in `src/rlrmp/analysis/induced_gain.py` with `feedbax_graph_controller(graph)` that wraps `graph._call_single_step` and uses `state.get(component.state_index)` to read the controller's substate. ~5–10 lines.\n2. Update tests in `tests/test_induced_gain.py` if they reference the old adapter API.\n3. **Audit recent rlrmp code** for any references to the old feedbax API: `Iterator`, `AbstractStagedModel`, `AbstractIterator`, `ModelInput`, `model.step`, `AbstractIntervenor`, etc. The user's concern: nothing has visibly broken because we haven't yet *run* anything against a real feedbax checkpoint with the new API; latent assumption mismatches may still exist. Files to grep specifically: `scripts/eval_*.py`, `scripts/train_*.py`, `src/rlrmp/**/*.py`.\n4. Note any findings in the issue comment thread; small fixes can land here, larger ones get their own issues.\n\nSurfaced from feedbax-architecture investigation. Reference: feedbax commit `1e5d8ec`, issues `f451fc4`, `4fcb0fc`.","files":null}]}